WEBVTT

00:02.123 --> 00:03.044
Meredith: TRAUMA IS MESSY...

00:03.044 --> 00:04.675
CHAOTIC.

00:04.675 --> 00:07.678
LOOKING AT A BODY THAT'S BEEN
REDUCED TO A BLOODY PULP...

00:09.050 --> 00:12.093
...IT MIGHT SEEM DIFFICULT
TO KNOW WHERE TO START.

00:12.093 --> 00:14.095
[ VOMITS ]

00:14.095 --> 00:16.016
EDWARDS,
GOT A VOMITER IN BED FIVE.

00:16.016 --> 00:17.598
RULE OUT OBSTRUCTION,
PLEASE?

00:17.598 --> 00:18.729
YAY!

00:18.729 --> 00:20.351
HOW WE DOING?
SHE'S IN
ALL RIGHT SHAPE,

00:20.351 --> 00:21.772
BUT SHE'S COMPLAINING
OF ABDOMINAL PAINS.

00:21.772 --> 00:24.065
OKAY. KEPNER,
WHAT DO YOU HAVE?

00:24.065 --> 00:25.066
MVC, BED THREE.

00:25.066 --> 00:26.067
SHEPHERD'S DOING
A NEURO CONSULT,

00:26.067 --> 00:27.818
BUT SHE JUST STARTED COMPLAINING
OF STOMACH PAIN.

00:27.818 --> 00:29.070
DR. PIERCE!
BUSY MORNING.

00:29.070 --> 00:30.651
YEAH, WHEN IT RAINS.

00:30.651 --> 00:32.993
HEY, CAN YOU GO SEE CHEST PAINS
IN BED SIX, PLEASE?
GOT IT.

00:32.993 --> 00:36.077
LUCKILY, SOME VERY CLEVER
PERSON DEVELOPED A PROTOCOL,

00:36.077 --> 00:39.250
THE ABCs --
AIRWAY, BREATHING, CIRCULATION.

00:39.250 --> 00:41.332
20-SOMETHING FEMALE
CARJACKING VICTIM --

00:41.332 --> 00:43.164
MULTIPLE LACS
AND CONTUSIONS,

00:43.164 --> 00:45.836
OPEN TIBIA FRACTURE,
HYPOTENSIVE AND TACHYCARDIC.

00:45.836 --> 00:47.588
[ SIGHS ]
THIS WAS A CARJACKING?

00:47.588 --> 00:49.760
AND A HELL OF A BEATING.
WILSON, YOU'RE WITH ME.

00:49.760 --> 00:51.842
THE ABCs
KEEP YOUR PATIENT ALIVE

00:51.842 --> 00:54.845
SO YOU CAN FIGURE OUT HOW
TO TACKLE THE REST OF THE MESS.

00:54.845 --> 00:56.437
IF ONLY ALL LIFE'S PROBLEMS

00:56.437 --> 00:58.179
COULD BE SOLVED
WITH AN INTUBATION TUBE.

00:58.179 --> 01:00.811
THEY TOOK MY CAR!

01:00.811 --> 01:02.183
OWEN: Shh, shh.
THEY TOOK MY --

01:02.183 --> 01:03.814
Shh, shh, shh, shh.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

01:03.814 --> 01:05.986
MELISSA. MY CAR --

01:05.986 --> 01:07.358
April: MELISSA,
I'M SURE YOUR CAR'S FINE.

01:07.358 --> 01:09.110
WE'RE GONNA TAKE CARE OF YOU,
OKAY?

01:09.110 --> 01:10.741
WILSON, GO SEE IF ANYONE
CAME IN WITH HER.

01:10.741 --> 01:12.113
OKAY.

01:14.115 --> 01:15.156
[ GROANS ]

01:16.197 --> 01:19.910
I THINK YOU'RE FINE,
BUT I WANT TO MAKE SURE.

01:19.910 --> 01:22.583
LET'S DO A HEAD C.T.
TO BE SAFE.
RIGHT AWAY.

01:22.583 --> 01:25.336
LET'S GET AN ABDOMINAL C.T.,
AS WELL.

01:25.336 --> 01:28.209
DR. GREY, I HAVE YOUR --
OUR...

01:28.209 --> 01:30.631
ELLIS' JOURNALS.

01:30.631 --> 01:32.173
YOU WENT THROUGH THEM
ALREADY?

01:32.173 --> 01:33.844
YEAH,
I'VE HAD THEM FOR A WHILE.

01:33.844 --> 01:36.177
GOT A GOOD SENSE OF HER
AS A SURGEON,

01:36.177 --> 01:39.019
IF NOT AS A PERSON.

01:39.019 --> 01:40.431
SO, THANK YOU.

01:40.431 --> 01:42.643
SURE.
OKAY.

01:44.104 --> 01:46.026
SHE STILL CALLS YOU
"DR. GREY"?

01:46.026 --> 01:48.569
THAT'S MY NAME.

01:48.569 --> 01:50.281
WE SHOULD INVITE HER OVER...
FOR DINNER.

01:50.281 --> 01:51.572
WHY?

01:51.572 --> 01:53.073
SHE'S FAMILY.
ISH.

01:53.073 --> 01:55.656
DINNER TOMORROW NIGHT.
IT'S WHAT PEOPLE DO.

01:55.656 --> 01:57.158
WHAT PEOPLE?

01:58.829 --> 02:01.542
[ SIGHS ] DR. HUNT IN TRAUMA ONE
NEEDS AN ORTHO CONSULT.

02:01.542 --> 02:02.703
Nurse: ON IT.

02:02.703 --> 02:04.165
APRIL.

02:04.165 --> 02:06.587
HEY, UH, I THOUGHT
YOU WERE ON THE --

02:06.587 --> 02:09.009
YEAH, YOUR MOM'S FLIGHT GOT IN
EARLY, SO I BROUGHT HER HERE.

02:09.009 --> 02:10.671
WHY WOULD YOU DO THAT?

02:10.671 --> 02:11.922
'CAUSE SHE WANTED TO SEE YOU.
WH--

02:11.922 --> 02:13.254
I-I SET HER UP
IN THE ATTENDINGS' LOUNGE.

02:13.254 --> 02:14.595
JUST GIVE ME A PAGE
WHEN YOU GET A SECOND.

02:14.595 --> 02:16.597
UH, I...
LOVE YOU!

02:16.597 --> 02:19.019
[ SIGHS ]
SORRY, UH, WHAT WAS I SAYING?

02:19.019 --> 02:20.431
THIS IS WHERE
YOU'VE BEEN STAYING?

02:20.431 --> 02:22.022
I FIGURED YOU'D GONE
TO A HOTEL, OR...

02:22.022 --> 02:23.814
YEAH, WELL, HERMAN'S
BEEN BREATHING DOWN
MY NECK DAY AND NIGHT.

02:23.814 --> 02:25.065
THIS IS EASIER.

02:25.065 --> 02:27.978
PLUS, WHERE I SLEEP IS
NO LONGER ANY OF YOUR CONCERN.

02:27.978 --> 02:30.611
I DIDN'T KICK YOU OUT.
I NEVER SAID THAT YOU HAD TO GO.

02:30.611 --> 02:32.072
NO, NO,
YOU JUST MADE IT VERY CLEAR

02:32.072 --> 02:33.484
THAT MY BEING AROUND YOU
WAS SUFFOCATING.

02:33.484 --> 02:34.825
[ CELLPHONE CHIMING ]

02:34.825 --> 02:38.038
[ SIGHS ] OKAY, WELL,
HAVE YOU TOLD ANYONE?

02:38.038 --> 02:39.910
NO. HAVE YOU?
NO.

02:39.910 --> 02:41.081
I -- DO YOU THINK
THAT WE SHOULD?

02:41.081 --> 02:44.585
CAN WE JUST NOT...
YET?

02:44.585 --> 02:46.126
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

02:46.126 --> 02:48.088
I DIDN'T WANT ANY OF THIS.

02:48.088 --> 02:50.000
I HAVE ROUNDS.

02:52.253 --> 02:54.755
I'M SAYING
YOU SKIPPED BREAKFAST.

02:54.755 --> 02:55.926
DIDN'T HAVE TIME!

02:55.926 --> 02:57.007
AVERY MADE ME
POINT PERSON

02:57.007 --> 02:58.889
ON THE BOARD'S
STRATEGIC PLANNING MEETING.

02:58.889 --> 03:00.010
AND I HAVE CONSULTS.

03:00.010 --> 03:02.012
GOT TO KEEP THE TRAINS
RUNNING ON TIME.

03:02.012 --> 03:03.013
AH-AH, AH-AH, AH-AH.

03:03.013 --> 03:04.435
AH. MM.

03:04.435 --> 03:06.066
YOU'RE MY FAVORITE
RESIDENT.

03:07.358 --> 03:08.359
HEY. YOU WERE LOOKING
FOR ME?

03:08.359 --> 03:09.570
YES.
MR. WEAVER HERE IS --

03:09.570 --> 03:10.731
OH, JEREMY.
HI.

03:10.731 --> 03:13.484
YEAH, HE'S COMPLAINING
OF CHEST PAINS.

03:13.484 --> 03:15.075
EKG IS FINE EXCEPT
FOR A LITTLE LVH,

03:15.075 --> 03:18.078
BUT HIS FIRST TROPONIN
IS WITHIN NORMAL LIMITS,

03:18.078 --> 03:19.119
SO I'VE RULED OUT
A DISSECTION,

03:19.119 --> 03:20.741
BUT HIS BELLY
IS STILL A LITTLE TENDER.

03:20.741 --> 03:22.082
I'M FINE, REALLY.

03:22.082 --> 03:23.083
OH, WELL, LET'S SEE.

03:23.083 --> 03:24.204
TAKE IT EASY,
MR. WEAVER.

03:24.204 --> 03:25.326
OKAY, SEE YOU LATER.

03:25.326 --> 03:27.248
OKAY.

03:27.248 --> 03:28.419
OW!

03:28.419 --> 03:29.880
HURTS THERE?

03:29.880 --> 03:31.962
YEAH, BUT IT'S --
IT'S HEARTBURN, I SWEAR.

03:31.962 --> 03:33.003
MY WIFE MADE ME COME.

03:33.003 --> 03:34.885
I MEAN, I SHOULD BE AT WORK,
YOU KNOW?

03:34.885 --> 03:36.547
AND I GOT TO
PICK UP MY KID LATER.

03:36.547 --> 03:37.548
[ GRUNTS ]

03:37.548 --> 03:39.099
UH, JEREMY,
HAVE YOU EATEN TODAY?

03:39.099 --> 03:40.180
UH, COFFEE.

03:40.180 --> 03:41.842
OH, YOU SKIPPED BREAKFAST,
TOO, HUH?

03:41.842 --> 03:43.894
UH, OH, NO, NO, NO,
AND THEN, UH, PANCAKES,

03:43.894 --> 03:45.936
SAUSAGE, EGGS,
A COUPLE OF ENERGY DRINKS.

03:45.936 --> 03:47.187
I WOULD'VE HAD MORE,

03:47.187 --> 03:48.559
BUT I'VE BEEN HAVING TROUBLE
SWALLOWING LATELY.

03:48.559 --> 03:50.060
Ben: SOUNDS LIKE YOU DID
PRETTY WELL.

03:50.060 --> 03:51.562
WELL, YOU GOT TO FUEL UP.

03:51.562 --> 03:52.693
YOU KNOW, I GOT A LOT
OF BALLS IN THE AIR!

03:52.693 --> 03:53.984
SORRY.

03:53.984 --> 03:55.656
LOOK, WE'RE GONNA ADMIT YOU
FOR OBSERVATION.

03:55.656 --> 03:56.737
NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO, NO.

03:56.737 --> 03:58.319
AND I'LL TRY
TO MAKE IT QUICK, OKAY?

03:58.319 --> 04:01.241
UM, ADD ON LFTs,
A SECOND TROPONIN,

04:01.241 --> 04:03.073
AND AN ABDOMINAL C.T.

04:03.073 --> 04:04.995
UH, CALL ME WHEN YOU GET
THE RESULTS.

04:04.995 --> 04:06.327
[ COUGHS ]
AH-AH, AH-AH, AH-AH.

04:06.327 --> 04:07.998
FINISH YOUR DOUGHNUT.

04:09.920 --> 04:11.081
MELISSA WORKS WITH US.

04:11.081 --> 04:13.294
WE DO COMPUTER REPAIR
AT OFFICE HUB.

04:13.294 --> 04:15.376
I FOUND HER
ON THE WAY INTO WORK.

04:15.376 --> 04:16.877
SHE WAS JUST LAYING THERE
ON THE GROUND, NOT MOVING.

04:16.877 --> 04:18.218
I THOUGHT SHE WAS DEAD!

04:18.218 --> 04:20.931
DO YOU KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT HER
FAMILY, ANYONE WE CAN CONTACT?

04:22.092 --> 04:23.554
WE DON'T REALLY KNOW HER
THAT WELL.

04:23.554 --> 04:25.055
Owen: WILSON!

04:25.055 --> 04:27.017
UH, WHY DON'T YOU GUYS
TAKE A SEAT? I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

04:27.017 --> 04:28.599
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
SHE'S CRASHING.

04:28.599 --> 04:30.771
YOU PAGED ORTHO?
OH, WHOA!

04:30.771 --> 04:31.982
YEAH,
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO WAIT.

04:31.982 --> 04:33.394
BELLY'S EXPANDING EVEN THOUGH
I CROSS-CLAMPED THE AORTA.

04:33.394 --> 04:35.065
SHOULD WE BOOK AN O.R.?

04:35.065 --> 04:36.987
YEAH, BUT SHE'S NOT GONNA
MAKE IT TO AN O.R. WITH
THIS MUCH BLOOD IN THE BELLY.

04:36.987 --> 04:38.859
WE'RE GONNA NEED TO DO
AN EMERGENCY LAPAROTOMY.

04:38.859 --> 04:40.200
UH, RIGHT NOW?
HERE?

04:40.200 --> 04:43.033
WILSON,
WE'RE GONNA NEED GAUZE, LAPS,

04:43.033 --> 04:45.115
WHATEVER WE HAVE
TO PACK THIS ABDOMEN.

04:48.038 --> 04:49.169
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

04:50.671 --> 04:53.003
YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO DO THIS?

04:53.003 --> 04:56.046
I'M SURE
WE DON'T HAVE A CHOICE.

04:56.046 --> 04:57.758
OKAY.

05:00.421 --> 05:01.592
OH!

05:01.592 --> 05:03.594
[ MONITORS BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

05:14.485 --> 05:15.896
ALL RIGHT, WILSON.
LIVER'S INTACT.

05:15.896 --> 05:18.699
LET'S LOOK
AT THE RETROPERITONEUM.

05:18.699 --> 05:21.742
OH, GOD,
IT'S THE I.V.C.

05:21.742 --> 05:22.823
OKAY,
PUT SOME PRESSURE ON IT.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.825
SATINSKY, PLEASE.
SUCTION READY.

05:24.825 --> 05:26.577
ALL RIGHT, FRACTURE'S ALL
CLEANED OUT FOR NOW.

05:26.577 --> 05:28.158
I'LL DO THE REPAIR
TOMORROW.

05:28.158 --> 05:29.910
HAVE WE FOUND OUT ANYTHING
ABOUT THIS GIRL?

05:29.910 --> 05:31.081
NO PURSE, NO I.D.

05:31.081 --> 05:32.413
AND WE KNOW SHE WORKED
AT THE OFFICE HUB,

05:32.413 --> 05:34.585
BUT THE ONLY EMERGENCY CONTACT
THEY HAD WAS HER OWN NUMBER.

05:34.585 --> 05:36.166
ACTUALLY,
WE KNOW SOMETHING ELSE.

05:36.166 --> 05:38.168
SHE'S A VETERAN.

05:38.168 --> 05:41.131
YEAH, SHE HAS AN OPERATION IRAQI
FREEDOM TATTOO, 2011-2012.

05:41.131 --> 05:43.554
I'VE BEEN EXAMINING A LOT
OF VETS LATELY, THANKS TO YOU.

05:43.554 --> 05:44.635
GOOD EYE, TORRES.

05:44.635 --> 05:46.637
THE INJURY'S EXPOSED.
4-OH PROLENE.

05:46.637 --> 05:49.139
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

05:49.139 --> 05:51.141
[ SIGHS ] THIS SHOULD NEVER
HAVE HAPPENED TO HER.

05:51.141 --> 05:52.643
IT SHOULDN'T HAVE HAPPENED
TO ANYONE.

05:54.024 --> 05:55.025
MORE SUCTION, PLEASE.

05:56.687 --> 05:58.318
HI, MOM!

05:58.318 --> 06:00.941
AH! [ LAUGHS ]

06:00.941 --> 06:02.072
AH!

06:02.072 --> 06:03.984
OH, LOOK AT --
OH, LOOK AT YOU!

06:03.984 --> 06:05.155
OH!

06:05.155 --> 06:06.326
HOW WAS YOUR FLIGHT?

06:06.326 --> 06:08.158
OH, NOT AS GOOD
AS MY RIDE OVER.

06:08.158 --> 06:10.160
MY CHAUFFEUR
HAS THE PRETTIEST EYES.

06:10.160 --> 06:11.331
MOM!

06:11.331 --> 06:13.123
OH, UH, THANK YOU?

06:13.123 --> 06:15.375
[ GASPS ]
OH, LOOK, I ALMOST FORGOT.

06:15.375 --> 06:18.709
LOOK WHAT I FOUND
IN THE AIRPORT GIFT SHOP --

06:18.709 --> 06:22.302
ZOO ANIMAL DECALS
FROM THE SEATTLE ZOO!

06:22.302 --> 06:25.055
I THOUGHT THEY'D BE ADORABLE
ON THE NURSERY WALL,

06:25.055 --> 06:26.717
AND THEY'LL GO WITH
WHATEVER COLOR

06:26.717 --> 06:28.098
YOU'RE
PLANNING ON PAINTING,

06:28.098 --> 06:30.350
WHICH I ASSUME
IS GENDER NEUTRAL.

06:30.350 --> 06:32.062
OH, YOU KNOW, ACTUALLY,
WE HAVEN'T --

06:32.062 --> 06:33.854
WE HAVEN'T REALLY HAD TIME
TO THINK ABOUT COLORS.

06:33.854 --> 06:34.975
MNH-MNH.

06:34.975 --> 06:37.818
OH, YOU TWO AND WORK --
BUSY, BUSY, BUSY!

06:37.818 --> 06:40.651
SPEAKING OF WHICH, UM,
THE E.R. IS A MADHOUSE.

06:40.651 --> 06:42.072
OH, YEAH.

06:42.072 --> 06:44.485
I-I PROBABLY -- I JUST NEED
TO GET BACK DOWN THERE,

06:44.485 --> 06:47.197
BUT I PROMISE I WILL TRY
TO MAKE IT BACK FOR DINNER.

06:47.197 --> 06:48.699
OH, DINNER?

06:48.699 --> 06:52.082
MOM....WHAT?

06:52.082 --> 06:55.165
I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU COULD
TAKE OFF THE AFTERNOON.

06:55.165 --> 06:57.297
WE COULD SHOP FOR PAINT SAMPLES
FOR THE NURSERY

06:57.297 --> 06:58.459
AND OPEN A BABY REGISTRY.

06:58.459 --> 07:00.090
MRS. FRYE AT CHURCH
ASKS OVER --

07:00.090 --> 07:01.842
MOM, YOU KNOW WHAT I DO
FOR A LIVING.

07:01.842 --> 07:03.253
I DON'T KNOW WHY YOU
THOUGHT I COULD JUST TAKE
ALL AFTERNOON OFF TO --

07:03.253 --> 07:04.545
YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:04.545 --> 07:06.847
I HAVE
A SUPER-LIGHT DAY,

07:06.847 --> 07:08.809
SO I CAN -- I CAN DO ALL OF --
ALL OF THOSE THINGS.

07:08.809 --> 07:10.390
JACKSON, YOU D--
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

07:10.390 --> 07:12.182
IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

07:12.182 --> 07:13.724
IT'LL BE FUN!

07:13.724 --> 07:15.105
YES, IT WILL.

07:15.105 --> 07:16.436
WE'VE GOT THIS.

07:18.398 --> 07:20.020
GUYS, I DON'T WANT
TO SOUND LIKE A JERK,

07:20.020 --> 07:21.862
BUT I GOT CLIENTS TO SEE
ALL OVER TOWN,

07:21.862 --> 07:24.114
AND THEN I GOT TO PICK UP MY KID
AND DROP HER AT VOLLEYBALL,

07:24.114 --> 07:25.946
AND THEN I GOT
TWO MORE CLIENTS TO SEE.

07:25.946 --> 07:27.157
AND BELIEVE ME, I GET IT.

07:27.157 --> 07:28.739
THE NUMBER OF THINGS I'VE GOT
ON MY AGENDA

07:28.739 --> 07:30.200
WOULD MAKE YOUR HEAD SPIN.

07:30.200 --> 07:32.032
PERFECT -- THEN SEND ME HOME,
AND WE CAN BOTH GET BACK TO IT.

07:32.032 --> 07:34.414
I MEAN, LOOK AT ME.
I'M FIT AS A FIDDLE.

07:34.414 --> 07:35.916
WELL, THAT'S NOT
WHAT YOUR LABS SAY.

07:35.916 --> 07:38.629
UH, CHOLESTEROL
IS IN THE 300s.

07:38.629 --> 07:40.080
YOUR TRIGLYCERIDES
ARE WORSE.

07:40.080 --> 07:42.462
YOUR BP's TOO HIGH,
AND YOUR BLOOD SUGAR

07:42.462 --> 07:44.214
IS IN
THE PRE-DIABETIC RANGE.

07:44.214 --> 07:47.798
WHO ARE YOU GONNA BELIEVE --
ME OR SCIENCE?

07:47.798 --> 07:49.590
OKAY,
YOU'VE GOT AN HONEST FACE,

07:49.590 --> 07:51.261
BUT SCIENCE AND I
GO WAY BACK.

07:51.261 --> 07:53.223
C.T. DOESN'T SHOW
ABDOMINAL PROBLEMS,

07:53.223 --> 07:55.095
BUT WE'D LIKE TO DO
SOME EXTENSIVE STUDIES.

07:55.095 --> 07:57.648
[ SIGHS ]
SO WE NEED TO DO A BARIUM
SWALLOW TEST.

07:57.648 --> 08:00.060
WHEN WE GET THAT BACK,
DEPENDING ON THE RESULTS,

08:00.060 --> 08:02.232
I MIGHT NEED TO DO AN E.G.D.

08:02.232 --> 08:04.194
IS THERE ANY WAY
WE COULD SKIP A STEP,

08:04.194 --> 08:05.405
YOU KNOW,
CUT TO THE CHASE?

08:05.405 --> 08:06.867
[ LAUGHS ]
OKAY, DR. BAILEY

08:06.867 --> 08:09.820
IS JUST TRYING TO AVOID
PUTTING A TUBE DOWN YOUR THROAT

08:09.820 --> 08:11.241
OR UP YOUR, UH --

08:11.241 --> 08:12.743
OH. [ LAUGHS ]
INDEED.

08:12.743 --> 08:14.324
YOU KNOW,
I APPRECIATE THE THOUGHT,

08:14.324 --> 08:16.076
BUT IF IT'LL GET ME
OUT OF HERE SOONER,

08:16.076 --> 08:18.208
DR. BAILEY CAN STICK A TUBE
WHEREVER SHE WANTS.

08:19.830 --> 08:20.961
[ LAUGHS ]

08:20.961 --> 08:22.753
ALL RIGHT.

08:22.753 --> 08:25.385
THIS IS WALDO PFEIFFER,
GESTATIONAL AGE 23 WEEKS.

08:25.385 --> 08:28.178
IN ADDITION TO AN INCREDIBLY
UNFORTUNATE FIRST NAME,

08:28.178 --> 08:31.051
WALDO'S DEALING WITH
A PARTICULARLY NASTY C-CAM.

08:31.051 --> 08:33.013
TELL ME WHAT C-CAM
STANDS FOR.

08:33.013 --> 08:35.185
CONGENITAL CYSTIC ADENOMATOID
MALFORMATION.

08:35.185 --> 08:37.397
THE MASS IS PRESSING
ON HIS HEART AND LUNGS.

08:37.397 --> 08:39.600
WALDO'S C-CAM
HAS BEEN UNRESPONSIVE

08:39.600 --> 08:40.691
TO STEROID TREATMENT.

08:40.691 --> 08:42.102
NOW HE'S DEVELOPING
HYDROPS.

08:42.102 --> 08:43.984
THIS IS WHAT FETAL SURGERY
WAS CREATED FOR.

08:43.984 --> 08:45.646
FIRST, WE'RE GONNA
OPEN UP THE MOTHER,

08:45.646 --> 08:47.357
THEN INCISE THE UTERUS,

08:47.357 --> 08:49.409
THEN WE'RE GONNA REMOVE
THE C-CAM

08:49.409 --> 08:51.992
AND PUT HIM RIGHT BACK
WHERE WE FOUND HIM,

08:51.992 --> 08:54.154
AND HOPEFULLY
HE'LL BE CARRIED TO TERM.

08:54.154 --> 08:56.366
YOU HAVE A CONSULTATION
IN 20 MINUTES.

08:56.366 --> 08:58.328
MAKE IT FAST,
GET BACK HERE,

08:58.328 --> 09:01.371
AND WE'RE GOING TO GO OVER
THIS PROCEDURE STEP BY STEP.

09:01.371 --> 09:02.833
TERRIFIC.
THANK YOU.

09:02.833 --> 09:03.964
WELL, DON'T THANK ME.

09:03.964 --> 09:05.125
I DECIDED IT WAS NECESSARY

09:05.125 --> 09:07.798
WHEN IT TOOK YOU TWO MONTHS
TO WRAP YOUR HEAD AROUND

09:07.798 --> 09:08.969
A FETAL VALVULOPLASTY.

09:10.591 --> 09:11.672
YOU READY FOR THIS?

09:11.672 --> 09:14.224
YES.
YES, ABSOLUTELY.

09:16.056 --> 09:18.939
UH, IT'S A CHRONIC SUBDURAL.
IT SHOULD REABSORB ITSELF.

09:18.939 --> 09:20.440
GREAT. THANKS.

09:20.440 --> 09:25.065
YOUR WIFE INVITED ME
TO DINNER AT YOUR HOUSE.

09:25.065 --> 09:26.897
PERFECT.
[ LAUGHS ]

09:26.897 --> 09:28.859
YEAH, I WAS SO SURPRISED
BY THE INVITATION,

09:28.859 --> 09:30.821
I FORGOT TO ASK
IF I SHOULD BRING ANYTHING.

09:30.821 --> 09:32.783
JUST YOURSELF.
ANYTHING YOU DON'T EAT?

09:32.783 --> 09:34.404
NO. NOT AT ALL.

09:34.404 --> 09:35.786
OH, PERFECT.
[ LAUGHS ]

09:35.786 --> 09:36.787
HOW ABOUT A POT ROAST?

09:36.787 --> 09:38.078
GREAT.

09:38.078 --> 09:39.750
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

09:39.750 --> 09:41.832
UH, I'M -- I'M --
I'M SORRY.

09:41.832 --> 09:43.583
UH, SHEPHERD,
I WAS LOOKING FOR A CONSULT.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.085
I CAN COME BACK LATER.
NO, WE'RE DONE HERE.

09:45.085 --> 09:46.667
THANKS, DR. SHEPHERD.

09:48.799 --> 09:50.130
RICHARD.

09:51.051 --> 09:53.133
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
TOMORROW NIGHT?

09:53.133 --> 09:54.514
UM...

09:56.266 --> 09:59.720
HEY, THIS COULD BE YOU
IF YOU KEEP EATING LIKE YOU DO.

09:59.720 --> 10:02.272
I BET IF WE TOOK
YOUR BLOOD RIGHT NOW --

10:02.272 --> 10:05.726
MM-HMM, SEE, I COULD SAY
THE SAME THING ABOUT YOU,

10:05.726 --> 10:08.228
BUT I WOULDN'T WANT TO CHANGE
A SINGLE THING ABOUT YOU,

10:08.228 --> 10:09.609
SO I WON'T.

10:09.609 --> 10:12.072
I DON'T WANT TO CHANGE
ANYTHING ABOUT YOU EITHER.

10:12.072 --> 10:13.233
I LIKE YOU ALIVE,

10:13.233 --> 10:16.366
NOT DEAD ON A TOILET
AFTER HAVING A HEART ATTACK

10:16.366 --> 10:19.079
TRYING TO PASS
A DEEP-FRIED ONION BLOSSOM.

10:19.079 --> 10:21.872
GOD, MIRANDA,
WHY WOULD YOU EVEN THINK --

10:21.872 --> 10:22.873
WHAT THE HELL?

10:22.873 --> 10:24.835
OH, WHAT IS THIS?

10:24.835 --> 10:27.087
NOT A DEEP-FRIED ONION BLOSSOM
'CAUSE THAT'D JUST BE TOO MUCH.

10:27.087 --> 10:28.088
NO.

10:28.088 --> 10:30.340
IT'S A TUMOR.

10:30.340 --> 10:31.922
[ SIGHS ]

10:31.922 --> 10:33.804
AND IT'S A BIG ONE.

10:38.849 --> 10:40.020
HEY, SORRY,

10:40.020 --> 10:41.521
THE CONSULTATION WENT OFF
WITHOUT A HITCH,

10:41.521 --> 10:42.853
BUT THEN MOM GOT
A LITTLE NERVOUS,

10:42.853 --> 10:44.564
SO I JUST WANTED TO MAKE SURE
THAT SHE WAS OKAY.

10:44.564 --> 10:45.766
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

10:45.766 --> 10:46.977
C-CAM.

10:46.977 --> 10:49.229
UM, I'M READY
WHENEVER YOU ARE.

10:49.229 --> 10:51.231
THERE'S BEEN
A CHANGE IN PLANS.

10:51.231 --> 10:53.363
I'M HAVING A PERSONAL...

10:53.363 --> 10:54.945
I'M GOING HOME.

10:54.945 --> 10:57.117
HERE ARE THE MATERIALS
ON THE PROCEDURE.

10:57.117 --> 10:58.538
INTERNALIZE THEM.

10:58.538 --> 11:01.161
I'VE MADE NOTES IN THE MARGINS
BECAUSE MY APPROACH IS BETTER

11:01.161 --> 11:02.703
THAN MOST OF THE CRAP
THAT'S IN THERE.

11:02.703 --> 11:04.084
YOU'LL ALSO NEED
TO COVER MY SERVICE.

11:04.084 --> 11:06.456
WAIT, HOLD ON.
IS EVERYTHING, UH, OKAY?

11:06.456 --> 11:07.748
I SAID IT'S PERSONAL!

11:07.748 --> 11:09.339
YOU HAVE WHAT YOU NEED
FROM ME THERE.

11:09.339 --> 11:11.001
READ IT.
WHAT IF I HAVE QUESTIONS?

11:11.001 --> 11:13.253
THEY'LL BE ANSWERED IN THERE.
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

11:15.425 --> 11:17.297
Woman: I KEEP TELLING YOU
TO TAKE MORE WALKS,

11:17.297 --> 11:19.389
YEAH, YOU KNOW, I MEAN, LIKE,
HAVE A SALAD, MAYBE,

11:19.389 --> 11:21.011
INSTEAD OF ALL
THE PHILLY CHEESESTEAKS.

11:21.011 --> 11:22.682
Jeremy: YOU CERTAINLY DO,
HONEY, CONSTANTLY,

11:22.682 --> 11:25.395
AND JUST EVERY TIME --
HELLO.

11:27.898 --> 11:29.810
YOU DON'T LOOK LIKE
YOU HAVE GOOD NEWS.

11:29.810 --> 11:32.072
JEREMY [SIGHS]

11:32.072 --> 11:36.076
UM, I'M AFRAID THE E.G.D.
REVEALED A TUMOR.

11:36.076 --> 11:38.739
IT'S EARLY-STAGE
ADENOCARCINOMA.

11:38.739 --> 11:41.161
OH, GOD!
CANCER?

11:41.161 --> 11:43.914
BUT I-I-I CAME IN HERE
FOR HEARTBURN.

11:43.914 --> 11:46.286
AND THAT'S MOST LIKELY
WHAT YOU HAD, BUT THE...

11:46.286 --> 11:49.129
CHEESESTEAKS
AND THE FRIED FOODS

11:49.129 --> 11:53.754
HAVE CAUSED INTENSE ACID REFLUX,
AND OVER TIME,

11:53.754 --> 11:56.046
THAT REFLUX
HAS MADE YOUR ESOPHAGUS

11:56.046 --> 11:58.008
THE PERFECT HOME FOR CANCER.

11:58.008 --> 11:59.009
I'M SORRY.

12:01.011 --> 12:02.012
SO, W-WHAT DO WE DO?

12:02.012 --> 12:03.343
WE'D LIKE
TO KEEP YOU OVERNIGHT

12:03.343 --> 12:05.015
AND DO SOME PRE-OP TESTS,

12:05.015 --> 12:07.107
THEN DO AN ESOPHAGECTOMY
WHERE WE REMOVE YOUR ESOPHAGUS

12:07.107 --> 12:09.149
AND REPLACE IT
WITH A PIECE OF YOUR COLON.

12:09.149 --> 12:10.520
AND THEN THE CANCER
WOULD BE GONE?

12:10.520 --> 12:11.902
THAT'S THE HOPE.

12:11.902 --> 12:13.904
YEAH, IT WILL BE.

12:13.904 --> 12:15.195
OKAY, IT'LL BE FINE.

12:15.195 --> 12:17.317
YOU GO AND GET ERIN.
YEAH.

12:17.317 --> 12:19.910
AND TELL HER WHAT'S GOING ON,
BUT DON'T SCARE HER, OKAY?

12:19.910 --> 12:21.161
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.
OKAY.

12:21.161 --> 12:22.532
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

12:22.532 --> 12:25.245
April:
HELLO, JACKSON?

12:25.245 --> 12:27.627
IN HERE, DR. MOM!

12:27.627 --> 12:29.209
[ LAUGHS ]

12:29.209 --> 12:30.420
HEY.
[ SIGHS ]

12:30.420 --> 12:32.002
WOW!

12:32.002 --> 12:33.713
YOU'VE BEEN...
BUSY.

12:33.713 --> 12:36.506
WE WERE JUST GONNA START
A GIFT REGISTRY,

12:36.506 --> 12:39.509
BUT THEN WE SAW
THIS ADORABLE MOBILE,

12:39.509 --> 12:42.012
AND THE NEXT THING I KNEW,
I FILLED A SHOPPING CART.

12:42.012 --> 12:43.263
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:43.263 --> 12:45.015
YEAH, WE ACTUALLY HAD
A PRETTY GOOD DAY TODAY.

12:45.015 --> 12:48.188
DON'T SOUND SO SURPRISED!
I AM QUITE FUN.

12:48.188 --> 12:51.311
UH, THIS DIDN'T COME
FROM A STORE.

12:51.311 --> 12:53.984
FOUR GENERATIONS
OF KEPNER BABIES

12:53.984 --> 12:56.236
HAVE SLEPT
IN THAT OLD WAR-HORSE.

12:56.236 --> 12:57.397
HOW DID YOU...

12:57.397 --> 13:00.070
YOU DIDN'T BRING THIS
IN YOUR CARRY-ON.

13:00.070 --> 13:01.902
SHIPPING COST A FORTUNE.

13:01.902 --> 13:03.864
YOUR SISTERS THOUGHT I SHOULD
SEND IT ALONG,

13:03.864 --> 13:06.166
BUT I WANTED TO BE HERE TO SEE
YOUR FACE WHEN IT ARRIVED,

13:06.166 --> 13:07.747
SO LAST WEEK,
I CALLED JACKSON.

13:07.747 --> 13:10.000
YOU CALLED JACKSON?!

13:10.000 --> 13:13.173
I DO KNOW HOW TO USE
A TELEPHONE, LITTLE MISS.

13:14.794 --> 13:17.587
[ SIGHS ]
I AM FAMISHED.

13:17.587 --> 13:18.758
WELL, WHY DID YOU WAIT FOR ME
TO EAT?

13:18.758 --> 13:20.090
I CALLED.
I TOLD YOU I'D BE LATE.

13:20.090 --> 13:22.382
WE PROBABLY JUST LOST
TRACK OF TIME.

13:22.382 --> 13:23.593
IT'S NO A BIG DEAL.

13:23.593 --> 13:24.925
I'LL JUST HOP IN THE KITCHEN
AND WHIP SOMETHING UP.

13:24.925 --> 13:26.186
WELL,
I DIDN'T GO TO THE STORE

13:26.186 --> 13:28.058
BECAUSE I THOUGHT THAT WE WOULD
BE GOING OUT.

13:28.058 --> 13:30.060
[ Laughing ] I'M SURE I CAN
FIGURE SOMETHING OUT.

13:30.060 --> 13:31.431
NO, NO, MOM, STOP IT!

13:31.431 --> 13:33.773
I DON'T -- I DON'T NEED YOU
TO WHIP SOMETHING UP,

13:33.773 --> 13:35.605
AND I DIDN'T NEED YOU
TO COME OUT HERE

13:35.605 --> 13:37.067
AND SET UP
MY WHOLE NURSERY.

13:37.067 --> 13:39.069
I DON'T NEED -- I --
I DON'T WANT YOUR HELP!

13:39.069 --> 13:40.070
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?!

13:40.070 --> 13:41.491
APRIL.

13:41.491 --> 13:43.113
COME ON, THAT'S NOT FAIR.

13:44.824 --> 13:46.496
Meredith:
YOU INVITED RICHARD TO DINNER?!

13:46.496 --> 13:48.658
THIS WAS ALREADY
A BAD IDEA.

13:48.658 --> 13:50.000
YOU'RE TRYING
TO MAKE IT WORSE?

13:50.000 --> 13:52.412
SHE DOESN'T WANT
TO KNOW HIM.

13:52.412 --> 13:54.004
HE SAID
EXACTLY THE SAME THING.

13:54.004 --> 13:56.046
OKAY, THEN WHY ARE YOU
TRYING TO FORCE IT?

13:56.046 --> 13:58.008
BECAUSE HE'S MY FRIEND.
HE'S OUR FRIEND.

13:58.008 --> 14:00.220
HE'S FAMILY,
AND THIS IS ONE OF THE REASONS

14:00.220 --> 14:02.132
WHY YOU DIDN'T WANT
TO LEAVE SEATTLE

14:02.132 --> 14:03.593
IN THE FIRST PLACE,
REMEMBER?

14:03.593 --> 14:05.015
YOU HAVE FAMILY HERE,
ROOTS.

14:05.015 --> 14:06.726
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?!

14:06.726 --> 14:08.889
WHAT? [ SIGHS ]

14:08.889 --> 14:11.021
I HAVE TO HAVE DINNER
WITH THE SISTER I DON'T KNOW

14:11.021 --> 14:12.102
AND THE BIO-DAD SHE HATES

14:12.102 --> 14:14.064
BECAUSE YOU GAVE UP YOUR CHANCE
TO WORK FOR OBAMA?!

14:14.064 --> 14:15.775
YOU'RE GONNA PLAY
THAT CARD?

14:15.775 --> 14:17.607
OF COURSE YOU ARE BECAUSE
YOU'LL BE PLAYING THAT CARD

14:17.607 --> 14:18.858
UNTIL THE END
OF FREAKING TIME!

14:18.858 --> 14:20.070
TIME-OUT.

14:20.070 --> 14:22.192
NO, I AM SO SICK OF YOUR
PASSIVE-AGGRESSIVE --

14:22.192 --> 14:24.154
TIME-OUT.
I'M SORRY.

14:24.154 --> 14:26.156
I SHOULDN'T HAVE SAID THAT.

14:26.156 --> 14:28.248
I AM JUST TRYING
TO HELP OUT HERE.

14:28.248 --> 14:31.201
I'M TRYING TO HELP YOU,
AND I AM TRYING TO HELP THEM.

14:31.201 --> 14:32.832
I COME FROM A BIG FAMILY.

14:32.832 --> 14:35.085
IT'S CRAZY, IT'S MESSY,
BUT IT'S GOOD,

14:35.085 --> 14:36.296
AND I WANT THAT FOR YOU.

14:36.296 --> 14:40.050
I WANT YOU TO HAVE THAT.

14:40.050 --> 14:41.381
SHE'S YOUR SISTER,

14:41.381 --> 14:43.803
AND HE'S PRACTICALLY
YOUR FATHER.

14:45.055 --> 14:47.557
AND ZOLA NEEDS
MORE BLACK PEOPLE IN THE FAMILY

14:47.557 --> 14:50.220
BECAUSE I'M RUNNING OUT OF WAYS
TO BRAID HER HAIR

14:50.220 --> 14:53.103
AND BAILEY WON'T SHOW ME
ANY MORE.

14:53.103 --> 14:59.069
♪ ALWAYS HOPEFUL
THAT I'LL MAKE A CHANGE ♪

14:59.069 --> 15:01.071
FINE.

15:01.071 --> 15:02.902
YOU WANT RICHARD
TO COME TO DINNER,

15:02.902 --> 15:04.324
CALL PIERCE AND MAKE SURE
SHE'S OKAY WITH IT.

15:04.324 --> 15:05.325
ME?

15:05.325 --> 15:07.077
YOU WANT RICHARD
TO COME TO DINNER.

15:07.077 --> 15:08.658
YOU WIN.
ACCEPT THE WIN.

15:08.658 --> 15:09.990
DON'T PUSH FOR MORE.

15:09.990 --> 15:13.163
OKAY, BUT S-SHOULDN'T YOU BE
THE ONE WHO'S MAKING THE --

15:13.163 --> 15:14.584
ACCEPT THE WIN.

15:14.584 --> 15:17.087
♪ ...HEART ♪

15:17.087 --> 15:19.749
♪ SO, I LOVE YOU ♪

15:19.749 --> 15:22.092
♪ I WANT YOU TO BE
ALL THAT YOU CAN ♪

15:22.092 --> 15:24.214
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
I THOUGHT I WAS CLEAR.

15:24.214 --> 15:26.256
I DON'T NEED YOU UP HERE
DOUBLE-CHECKING MY WORK.

15:26.256 --> 15:28.388
OH, DON'T GET ALL SHARKS
AND JETS ON ME, OKAY?

15:28.388 --> 15:30.220
ONE OF HERMAN'S PATIENTS
LANDED IN HERE,

15:30.220 --> 15:32.012
AND I'M LEARNING THE STEPS

15:32.012 --> 15:34.434
OF TOMORROW'S C-CAM FETAL
SURGERY FROM A JOURNAL ARTICLE.

15:34.434 --> 15:36.016
ACTUALLY, NOT EVEN --

15:36.016 --> 15:38.728
FROM THE CHICKEN SCRATCH
IN THE MARGIN OF AN ARTICLE.

15:38.728 --> 15:40.150
[ SIGHS ]

15:40.150 --> 15:42.062
I THINK SHE'S TRYING
TO HAZE ME [SIGHS]

15:42.062 --> 15:44.524
OR SET ME UP FOR A FAILURE
OR, UH, MAYBE KILL ME.

15:44.524 --> 15:46.026
YOU KNOW WHAT?

15:46.026 --> 15:47.157
NO ONE FORCED YOU TO DO THIS,
AND NOW YOU'RE GONNA POUT

15:47.157 --> 15:49.069
BECAUSE IT'S KIND OF HARD
AND YOUR TEACHER'S MEAN?

15:49.069 --> 15:50.160
SUCK IT UP.

15:50.160 --> 15:53.203
♪ ...DOWN ♪

15:53.203 --> 15:57.917
♪ WHAT YOU GONNA DO... ♪

15:57.917 --> 15:58.918
[ GASPS ]

15:58.918 --> 16:00.170
HEY.
[ GASPS ]

16:00.170 --> 16:02.172
MELISSA, IT'S OKAY.
WHAT ARE -- WHAT ARE YOU --

16:02.172 --> 16:04.004
Shh, YOU'RE -- YOU'RE --
YOU'RE IN THE HOSPITAL.

16:04.004 --> 16:05.425
YOU WERE --
WHERE'S --

16:05.425 --> 16:07.177
YOU WERE PRETTY BADLY BANGED UP,
BUT YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

16:07.177 --> 16:09.349
WHERE'S MY CAR?
D-DID THEY --

16:09.349 --> 16:10.510
IT'S --
DID THEY FIND MY CAR?

16:10.510 --> 16:12.182
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
DID THEY FIND MY CAR?

16:12.182 --> 16:14.144
Shh.
JUST TRY AND SLEEP.

16:14.144 --> 16:15.595
OKAY?

16:15.595 --> 16:17.097
Shh.

16:17.097 --> 16:20.770
♪ ...LOVING YOU ♪

16:25.315 --> 16:27.737
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

16:27.737 --> 16:30.070
DR. BAILEY!

16:30.070 --> 16:32.032
DR. PIERCE!

16:32.032 --> 16:33.533
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE A RUNNER!

16:33.533 --> 16:36.456
OH, YEAH.
I MEAN, I USUALLY JUST SPIN.

16:36.456 --> 16:38.168
I-I TAKE A SPIN CLASS.

16:38.168 --> 16:40.710
I THOUGHT I COULD GET SOME
FRESH AIR FOR A CHANGE.

16:40.710 --> 16:42.462
IT'S A GORGEOUS MORNING,
ISN'T IT?

16:42.462 --> 16:45.925
YOU KNOW, I WAS ONLY GONNA GO
LIKE ANOTHER 3 MILES,

16:45.925 --> 16:48.128
BUT I CAN STRETCH IT OUT
IF YOU WANT TO JOIN.

16:48.128 --> 16:50.130
OH, NO.
I MEAN, UH, THANK YOU.

16:50.130 --> 16:51.181
I -- I'M SORRY.

16:51.181 --> 16:53.133
I JUST PICKED UP
A NEW AUDIOBOOK.

16:53.133 --> 16:55.685
OPRAH RECOMMENDED IT.
TOTALLY UNDERSTAND.

16:55.685 --> 16:57.437
LET ME KNOW HOW IT IS.
OKAY.

17:00.400 --> 17:03.103
[ SIGHS ]

17:05.645 --> 17:07.907
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

17:07.907 --> 17:10.150
UH, YOU'RE THE LAST PERSON
WHO GETS TO LECTURE ME

17:10.150 --> 17:11.911
ON AVOIDING MY MOTHER.
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

17:11.911 --> 17:13.113
MY MOTHER IS A NIGHTMARE,

17:13.113 --> 17:15.205
AND YOURS IS THE SWEETEST PERSON
I'VE EVER MET.

17:15.205 --> 17:17.327
NO, WHAT HAPPENED LAST NIGHT
WAS NOT SWEET.

17:17.327 --> 17:18.498
IT WAS CONDESCENDING.

17:18.498 --> 17:20.080
COME ON,
YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

17:20.080 --> 17:22.582
YES, 'CAUSE SHE JUST DECIDED
THAT I NEEDED HER HELP.

17:22.582 --> 17:24.124
I NEEDED HELP.

17:24.124 --> 17:25.465
I ASKED HER FOR IT,
OKAY?

17:25.465 --> 17:27.797
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT THE HELL I'M DOING HERE.

17:27.797 --> 17:30.300
I JUST SPENT FOUR HOURS
IN THAT BABY STORE,

17:30.300 --> 17:31.931
AND MY MIND WAS BLOWN.

17:31.931 --> 17:35.265
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH I DON'T
KNOW ABOUT HAVING BABIES?

17:35.265 --> 17:36.726
SO MUCH.

17:36.726 --> 17:37.767
[ SIGHS ]

17:37.767 --> 17:39.309
AND SHE KNOWS EVERYTHING
AND SO DO YOU,

17:39.309 --> 17:40.810
AND IT'S EASY
FOR YOU GUYS.

17:40.810 --> 17:42.562
MY FAMILY WAS NOT BUILT
THAT WAY.

17:42.562 --> 17:44.234
I DIDN'T HAVE GRANDPARENTS
FALLING OVER THEMSELVES

17:44.234 --> 17:46.025
TRYING TO...LOVE ME,

17:46.025 --> 17:48.278
BUT LUCKY FOR US,
OUR KID WILL.

17:48.278 --> 17:52.402
THAT IS, PROVIDED THAT YOU DO
NOT DRIVE HER AWAY FIRST.

17:57.617 --> 17:58.998
HEY.
HEY, UH...

17:58.998 --> 18:01.331
O.R. THREE IS READY
FOR MELISSA'S TIBIA REPAIR,

18:01.331 --> 18:04.294
AND THE POLICE ARE FINISHING UP
GETTING HER STATEMENT NOW.

18:04.294 --> 18:07.086
ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU,
MA'AM.

18:07.086 --> 18:09.008
OH.

18:12.091 --> 18:13.843
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

18:13.843 --> 18:15.845
MELISSA,
ARE YOU OKAY?

18:15.845 --> 18:18.017
THEY FOUND IT.
[ SIGHS ]

18:18.017 --> 18:19.309
THEY FOUND MY CAR

18:19.309 --> 18:22.392
IN PIECES IN SOME CHOP SHOP
IN BELLEVUE,

18:22.392 --> 18:24.023
UM, AND IT'S GONE.

18:24.023 --> 18:26.396
OKAY. IT'S OKAY.
IT'S ALL REPLACEABLE.

18:26.396 --> 18:28.228
LET'S JUST BE GLAD
YOU DIDN'T GET KILLED.

18:28.228 --> 18:29.989
DAMN IT.

18:29.989 --> 18:31.821
IF I HADN'T BEEN
ASLEEP...

18:33.403 --> 18:35.785
WHAT HAPPENED?
DO YOU REMEMBER?

18:35.785 --> 18:36.946
I WAS SLEEPING,

18:36.946 --> 18:39.078
AND THEN
THEY BROKE THE WINDOW,

18:39.078 --> 18:41.791
AND THEY PULLED ME
OUT OF IT, AND...

18:41.791 --> 18:47.167
AND I TRIED TO HOLD ON,
BUT I GOT STUCK IN THE DOOR,

18:47.167 --> 18:50.920
AND THEY DRAGGED ME
FOR A WHILE,

18:50.920 --> 18:53.673
AND THEN THEY PUNCHED ME,
AND THEN THEY KICKED ME, AND...

18:53.673 --> 18:56.516
AND THEN I COULDN'T HOLD ON
ANYMORE.

18:56.516 --> 18:59.519
GOD, WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST
LET THEM TAKE IT?

18:59.519 --> 19:03.022
EVERYTHING
WAS IN THAT CAR.

19:05.225 --> 19:08.568
EVERYTHING.

19:08.568 --> 19:11.070
Jo: THE CAR WAS THE
FIRST THING SHE ASKED
ABOUT WHEN SHE WOKE UP.

19:11.070 --> 19:13.112
SHE SAID SHE WAS ASLEEP IN IT
WHEN SHE WAS ATTACKED.

19:13.112 --> 19:14.694
IT SOUNDS LIKE
IT'S ALL SHE HAD.

19:14.694 --> 19:16.155
SO YOU'RE SAYING
SHE'S HOMELESS?

19:16.155 --> 19:18.037
I'M SAYING I THINK SHE'S LIVING
IN HER CAR, SO, YEAH.

19:18.037 --> 19:20.740
WELL, I THOUGHT YOU SAID
SHE HAD A JOB.

19:20.740 --> 19:22.332
NO, YOU CAN HAVE A JOB
AND NOT HAVE A HOME.

19:22.332 --> 19:24.163
THAT JUST MAKES IT
EVEN WORSE.

19:24.163 --> 19:27.086
I MEAN, TRY GOING THROUGH
HIGH SCHOOL LIVING IN YOUR CAR.

19:27.086 --> 19:30.089
YOU GOT TO LIE ALL THE TIME,
YOU CAN NEVER HAVE ANYONE OVER,

19:30.089 --> 19:32.252
YOU HAVE TO MAKE UP EXCUSES WHY,
YOU HAVE NO BATHROOM,

19:32.252 --> 19:33.673
AND THEN YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:33.673 --> 19:35.054
YOU CAN'T EVEN TELL ANYBODY

19:35.054 --> 19:37.006
'CAUSE THEN THEY JUST
LOOK AT YOU LIKE YOU'RE
WEIRD AND PITIFUL.

19:37.006 --> 19:40.139
FIND ME
WHEN SHE WAKES UP.

19:40.139 --> 19:42.682
OKAY.

19:42.682 --> 19:44.514
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

19:45.895 --> 19:47.397
YOU LIVED IN YOUR CAR
IN HIGH SCHOOL?

19:47.397 --> 19:49.649
SEE, THAT'S THE LOOK.

19:59.579 --> 20:01.120
GLOVE ME.

20:01.120 --> 20:03.243
KAREV?

20:03.243 --> 20:05.034
DR. KAREV EXPRESSED
AN INTEREST

20:05.034 --> 20:06.706
IN OUR LITTLE
C-CAM SURGERY TODAY.

20:06.706 --> 20:08.127
YEAH,
IT SOUNDS AMAZING,

20:08.127 --> 20:09.379
BUT I WANT TO MAKE SURE
I'M NOT IN THE WAY.

20:09.379 --> 20:11.251
HAPPY TO HAVE YOU.

20:11.251 --> 20:14.334
HOPE TO HELL YOU STUDIED,
ROBBINS.

20:14.334 --> 20:17.006
I'LL WARN YOU,
I DID NOT SLEEP WELL LAST NIGHT.

20:17.006 --> 20:19.138
MY PATIENCE WILL BE THIN.

20:19.138 --> 20:21.761
RICHARD WEBBER
IS COMING?

20:21.761 --> 20:23.182
NO, THAT'S --

20:23.182 --> 20:24.934
I CAN'T BELIEVE HIM.

20:24.934 --> 20:26.936
NO, NO, NO. IT DIDN'T COME
FROM RICHARD, OKAY?

20:26.936 --> 20:28.017
I INVITED HIM.

20:28.017 --> 20:30.059
WELL, I CAN'T MAKE IT.
I'M SORRY.

20:30.059 --> 20:32.312
LOOK, YOU CAME HERE
TO FIND OUT ABOUT ELLIS.

20:32.312 --> 20:36.115
WHY DON'T YOU TALK TO SOMEONE
WHO ACTUALLY KNEW HER?

20:36.115 --> 20:37.066
TO RICHARD.

20:37.066 --> 20:39.319
COME AND HAVE DINNER
WITH ME AND MEREDITH.

20:39.319 --> 20:41.120
LESS PRESSURE --
IT'S A BABY STEP.

20:41.120 --> 20:42.862
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

20:44.123 --> 20:46.456
LET ME THINK ABOUT IT.

20:46.456 --> 20:48.538
OKAY.

20:48.538 --> 20:51.210
[ SIGHS ]

20:53.673 --> 20:56.506
IS THIS ABOUT HOW I'M GONNA
PAY FOR ALL THIS?

20:56.506 --> 20:58.838
NO. NO, NO, NO.

20:58.838 --> 21:00.179
WE JUST WANTED TO KNOW --

21:00.179 --> 21:02.762
'CAUSE I-I HAVE
SOME INSURANCE LEFT,

21:02.762 --> 21:04.263
BUT ALL THE PAPERWORK WAS --

21:04.263 --> 21:06.185
WAS INSIDE YOUR CAR?

21:06.185 --> 21:08.848
I'M JUST SAYING
THAT I'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

21:08.848 --> 21:10.350
MELISSA,
ARE YOU LIVING IN YOUR CAR?

21:11.521 --> 21:12.522
WILSON.

21:12.522 --> 21:13.813
I DON'T KNOW
HOW ELSE TO ASK.

21:13.813 --> 21:15.234
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
WE DON'T MEAN TO PRY.

21:15.234 --> 21:16.736
WE JUST --
I --

21:16.736 --> 21:18.398
I-IT WAS ONLY GONNA BE
TEMPORARY.

21:18.398 --> 21:20.610
I -- WHEN I GOT OUT
OF THE ARMY,

21:20.610 --> 21:22.822
THE JOB I HAD LINED UP
WAS GONE.

21:22.822 --> 21:24.664
MY FIANCé WAS GONE,
AND...

21:24.664 --> 21:26.536
MY APARTMENT WITH HIM.

21:26.536 --> 21:29.078
ALL I COULD GET
WAS THE JOB AT OFFICE HUB,

21:29.078 --> 21:32.001
AND IT DOESN'T PAY GREAT,
AND I COULDN'T AFFORD RENT,

21:32.001 --> 21:35.174
SO, YEAH,
I'M MAKING IT WORK.

21:35.174 --> 21:39.339
BUT NOW THE CAR'S GONE WITH,
UH, MY CASH [SIGHS]

21:39.339 --> 21:41.591
AND MY CLOTHES,
MY SAVINGS

21:41.591 --> 21:44.424
'CAUSE BANKS WANT YOU TO HAVE
AN ADDRESS.

21:44.424 --> 21:47.096
UM...

21:47.096 --> 21:50.189
SO, UH, YEAH.

21:50.189 --> 21:51.771
YEAH.

21:51.771 --> 21:54.273
I MEAN,
EVERYTHING I HAVE IS GONE,

21:54.273 --> 21:56.936
BUT IF I CAN'T
GET BACK TO WORK,

21:56.936 --> 21:59.359
THEN I'M GONNA LOSE
MY JOB, TOO.

21:59.359 --> 22:01.070
[ SIGHS ]

22:01.070 --> 22:03.282
MELISSA,
THERE ARE PROGRAMS AVAILABLE

22:03.282 --> 22:05.074
FOR THE SOLE PURPOSE
OF HELPING...

22:05.074 --> 22:06.406
HOMELESS VETERANS.

22:06.406 --> 22:09.999
WELL, I'M NOT HOMELESS.
I'M -- IT'S ONLY TEMPORARY.

22:09.999 --> 22:13.082
THEY WILL GET YOU INTO REAL,
DEPENDABLE HOUSING,

22:13.082 --> 22:15.084
THEN AFTER THAT, EVERYTHING ELSE
IS THAT MUCH EASIER.

22:15.084 --> 22:16.876
SEE, THAT'S --
THAT'S NOT FOR ME.

22:16.876 --> 22:19.048
YOU SERVED IN IRAQ.

22:19.048 --> 22:20.800
I FIXED COMPUTERS
IN AN OPERATIONS OFFICE

22:20.800 --> 22:22.011
IN THE GREEN ZONE.

22:22.011 --> 22:24.424
THERE ARE GUYS
WHO WERE WOUNDED IN COMBAT,

22:24.424 --> 22:27.767
WHO WERE BLOWN TO PIECES,
WHO HAD THEIR FACES BURNED OFF,

22:27.767 --> 22:32.061
AND I'VE MET GUYS WHO HAVE BEEN
ON THE STREET SINCE VIETNAM.

22:32.061 --> 22:33.973
I WAS CARJACKED.

22:33.973 --> 22:35.525
IN SEATTLE.
[ SCOFFS ]

22:35.525 --> 22:37.817
EXCUSE ME.

22:37.817 --> 22:39.979
YOU HAVE SOME VISITORS.

22:44.323 --> 22:46.245
[ SIGHS ]

22:46.245 --> 22:48.077
OH, MY GOD, UH...

22:48.077 --> 22:50.249
JUST, UH, P-PLEASE GO?

22:50.249 --> 22:53.793
AND DON'T SAY A WORD
TO THOSE GUYS?

22:58.498 --> 23:01.050
MELISSA, I --
I'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

23:02.552 --> 23:04.634
I ALWAYS DO.

23:06.215 --> 23:07.927
JUST GO, PLEASE.

23:13.182 --> 23:17.106
OKAY, EVERYBODY,
WE'RE ABOUT TO MEET WALDO.

23:17.106 --> 23:20.440
LET'S BE QUIET
SO WE DON'T WAKE HIM UP.

23:24.984 --> 23:26.786
ROBBINS, NEXT STEP?

23:26.786 --> 23:29.328
A 20-CC-PER-KILO BOLUS
OF NORMAL SALINE

23:29.328 --> 23:30.490
INTO THE UMBILICAL VEIN.

23:30.490 --> 23:32.582
SO YOU DID READ MY NOTES.

23:32.582 --> 23:35.204
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'LL GIVE THE BOLUS.

23:35.204 --> 23:38.127
YOU PULL OUT WALDO'S ARM
SO WE CAN ATTACH THE MONITOR.

23:50.760 --> 23:52.812
OKAY.

23:52.812 --> 23:54.143
IT'S AMAZING.

23:54.143 --> 23:55.605
INDEED.

23:55.605 --> 23:58.267
NOW YOU'RE READY FOR
CHEST EXPOSURE AND INCISION.

23:58.267 --> 23:59.819
SCALPEL.

23:59.819 --> 24:01.150
NOW,
EVERY STEP COUNTS HERE.

24:01.150 --> 24:02.482
TELL ME
WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO DO.

24:02.482 --> 24:04.944
I'LL PERFORM A POSTEROLATERAL
THORACOTOMY

24:04.944 --> 24:06.405
AND SLOWLY DELIVER
THE MASS.

24:06.405 --> 24:08.197
SLOWLY AND CONTROLLED.

24:08.197 --> 24:09.829
I'M SORRY?
MY NOTES SAID

24:09.829 --> 24:12.161
THE MASS NEEDS TO BE
DELIVERED SLOWLY

24:12.161 --> 24:14.073
AND IN
A CONTROLLED MANNER.

24:14.073 --> 24:15.835
DID YOU READ MY NOTES
OR NOT?

24:15.835 --> 24:18.918
I DID. IT ALSO TOLD ME
TO PREPARE FOR BRADYCARDIA.

24:18.918 --> 24:20.840
[ MONITORS BEEPING ]

24:21.921 --> 24:23.753
PROCEED.

24:26.295 --> 24:29.138
OKAY.
THERE'S THE MASS.

24:29.138 --> 24:30.089
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

24:30.089 --> 24:31.300
AND THERE'S
THE BRADYCARDIA.

24:31.300 --> 24:32.471
HOW DO WE HANDLE THAT?

24:32.471 --> 24:34.514
ATROPINE AND EPI I.M.
INTO THE DELTOID.

24:34.514 --> 24:36.516
AND WHY IS THIS IMPORTANT?
WHY THIS APPROACH?

24:36.516 --> 24:38.227
'CAUSE IF THE C-CAM
STARTS TO POP OUT,

24:38.227 --> 24:40.439
THEN THIS LITTLE GUY IS AT RISK
FOR HEART FAILURE.

24:40.439 --> 24:43.102
THAT'S NOT
WHAT MY NOTES SAID.

24:43.102 --> 24:44.023
WELL, NOT IN THOSE WORDS,
BUT --

24:44.023 --> 24:46.195
I WANT MY WORDS.
I WANT MY EXACT WORDS.

24:46.195 --> 24:48.197
YOU'RE GIVING ME
THE GIST.

24:48.197 --> 24:50.990
I'M NOT INTERESTED IN YOUR
INTERPRETATION OF MY NOTES.

24:50.990 --> 24:54.574
I WANT TO KNOW THAT
THE SPECIFIC WORDS THAT I WROTE

24:54.574 --> 24:56.165
ARE NOW EMBEDDED
IN YOUR BRAIN.

24:56.165 --> 24:57.917
THAT'S WHAT THIS
IS ALL ABOUT.

24:57.917 --> 24:59.999
THAT'S WHAT THIS FELLOWSHIP
IS ALL ABOUT.

24:59.999 --> 25:01.671
IF YOU'RE ONLY INTERESTED
IN LEARNING THE GIST OF --

25:01.671 --> 25:04.213
ALL RIGHT,
SHE GETS THE POINT.

25:04.213 --> 25:06.085
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

25:06.085 --> 25:07.927
DR. KAREV...

25:07.927 --> 25:10.469
WE'RE JUST GETTING
TO THE GOOD PART.

25:10.469 --> 25:13.763
YOU DON'T WANT
TO HAVE TO LEAVE NOW.

25:13.763 --> 25:17.136
MY NOTES SAID
THAT BEFORE MY APPROACH,

25:17.136 --> 25:19.979
THIS SURGERY RESULTED
IN FETAL CARDIAC ARREST

25:19.979 --> 25:22.231
50% OF THE TIME.

25:22.231 --> 25:25.064
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

25:26.986 --> 25:28.988
FEELS STRANGE,
DOESN'T IT?

25:28.988 --> 25:31.701
TO TOUCH A BABY
BEFORE HE'S EVEN BORN?

25:31.701 --> 25:35.494
YOU KNOW
WHAT IT FEELS LIKE?

25:35.494 --> 25:38.157
PRIVILEGE.

25:38.157 --> 25:40.119
GREAT PRIVILEGE.

25:47.166 --> 25:51.170
[ INDISTINCT P.A. ANNOUNCEMENT ]

25:51.170 --> 25:52.672
UM [CLEARS THROAT]

25:52.672 --> 25:54.173
OKAY.
WHAT HAPPENED?

25:54.173 --> 25:55.344
NOTHING.

25:55.344 --> 25:57.176
DID YOU FALL?

25:57.176 --> 25:58.437
[ SCOFFS ] NO!

25:58.437 --> 26:00.019
I'M FINE.

26:00.019 --> 26:01.350
YOU'RE NOT FINE.

26:01.350 --> 26:03.683
YOU'RE --
YOU'RE LIMPING.

26:03.683 --> 26:07.396
LIMPING? I HOPE YOU DIDN'T
OVERDO IT THIS MORNING.

26:07.396 --> 26:08.567
OVERDO WHAT?

26:08.567 --> 26:09.689
JOGGING.

26:09.689 --> 26:10.820
JOGGING?

26:10.820 --> 26:12.241
YES, JOGGING.

26:12.241 --> 26:14.403
SHE DIDN'T TELL YOU?

26:14.403 --> 26:17.076
WE RAN INTO EACH OTHER
AT THE SEWARD PARK TRAIL.

26:17.076 --> 26:18.537
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
MNH-MNH.

26:21.330 --> 26:24.413
ARE WE GONNA GO GET A TUMOR
OUT OF A MAN

26:24.413 --> 26:26.916
OR JUST SIT AROUND
AND TALK ABOUT IT?

26:28.668 --> 26:31.590
OKAY.
MEREDITH.

26:31.590 --> 26:34.013
DID DEREK TALK TO YOU ABOUT
ME COMING TO THIS DINNER?

26:34.013 --> 26:35.885
HE DID.
OKAY, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

26:35.885 --> 26:37.386
BECAUSE I'M NOT
100% CONVINCED.

26:37.386 --> 26:38.517
I'M NOT EITHER.

26:38.517 --> 26:40.269
I-I THINK IT MIGHT SEEM --
A LITTLE PUSHY.

26:40.269 --> 26:41.811
A LITTLE TOO MUCH,
TOO SOON.

26:41.811 --> 26:43.352
I'M THINKING
OF CALLING IT OFF.

26:43.352 --> 26:44.934
WELL,
IF YOU THINK THAT'S BEST.

26:44.934 --> 26:46.355
I THINK
DEREK WILL UNDERSTAND.

26:46.355 --> 26:48.107
WHAT IS WRONG
WITH YOU PEOPLE?!

26:48.107 --> 26:49.939
YOU CAN'T UN-INVITE SOMEONE
TO DINNER,

26:49.939 --> 26:51.901
NOT AFTER THE SONG AND DANCE
I HAD TO GO THROUGH

26:51.901 --> 26:53.402
TO GET HER
TO EVEN THINK ABOUT COMING.

26:53.402 --> 26:55.735
YOU'RE NOT CALLING THIS OFF!

26:55.735 --> 26:58.828
OKAY, I HAVE AN ANEURYSM
I NEED TO CLIP.

26:58.828 --> 27:01.200
I WILL SEE YOU BOTH THERE
TONIGHT.

27:03.502 --> 27:05.164
I'LL BRING DESSERT.

27:05.164 --> 27:07.336
THANKS.
THAT WOULD BE NICE.

27:07.336 --> 27:09.669
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

27:09.669 --> 27:12.511
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

27:12.511 --> 27:14.844
EDWARDS, START HIS WORK-UP.
I'LL BE THERE IN A SECOND.

27:14.844 --> 27:16.425
COPY THAT.

27:16.425 --> 27:20.099
Man: 47-YEAR-OLD MALE. HE WAS
THE PASSENGER IN A VEHICLE.

27:21.350 --> 27:24.023
I THOUGHT YOUR FLIGHT WASN'T
TILL LATER THIS AFTERNOON.

27:24.023 --> 27:25.524
I PUSHED IT.

27:25.524 --> 27:27.977
YOU OWE ME AN APOLOGY.

27:27.977 --> 27:30.319
AND I'M NOT LEAVING
UNTIL I GET ONE.

27:30.319 --> 27:32.111
I OWE YOU AN APOLOGY?

27:32.111 --> 27:35.034
YOU WERE RUDE,
AND I RAISED YOU BETTER.

27:35.034 --> 27:36.445
I UNDERSTAND
YOU'RE VERY BUSY,

27:36.445 --> 27:39.118
AND I UNDERSTAND
YOU WORK HARD, BUT --

27:39.118 --> 27:40.329
MOM,
I AM NOT GOING TO APOLOGIZE

27:40.329 --> 27:42.121
FOR HAVING THE LIFE THAT I WANT,
EVEN IF YOU THINK --

27:42.121 --> 27:43.993
APRIL KEPNER!

27:43.993 --> 27:47.837
YOU HAVE MADE CHOICES THAT
ARE VERY DIFFERENT FROM MINE,

27:47.837 --> 27:49.839
AND IT'S SCARY.

27:49.839 --> 27:52.752
ANY MOTHER
WHO WATCHES HER CHILD

27:52.752 --> 27:56.055
DO SOMETHING
SHE HASN'T DONE HERSELF --

27:56.055 --> 27:57.466
IT'S SCARY.

27:57.466 --> 28:00.429
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
I HAVEN'T BEEN PROUD OF YOU,

28:00.429 --> 28:05.895
AND THE MORE I SEE YOU
IN THIS WORLD, IN THIS WORK,

28:05.895 --> 28:08.017
IN THIS MARRIAGE...

28:08.017 --> 28:10.019
THE PROUDER I AM.

28:10.019 --> 28:14.734
I HAVE NO EARTHLY UNDERSTANDING
OF WHAT IT IS YOU DO,

28:14.734 --> 28:16.315
BUT I KNOW
A LOT ABOUT BABIES,

28:16.315 --> 28:18.908
AND I DON'T WANT TO TAKE
ANYTHING AWAY FROM YOU.

28:18.908 --> 28:21.320
I JUST WANT TO HELP YOU.

28:21.320 --> 28:26.035
AND I GET TO DO THAT
BECAUSE I AM A GRANDMA.

28:27.586 --> 28:31.590
AND I AM ALSO...
YOUR MOTHER.

28:37.006 --> 28:39.929
[ SIGHS ]

28:39.929 --> 28:42.802
I'M SORRY.

28:42.802 --> 28:45.684
THANK YOU.

28:47.186 --> 28:49.018
SO, CAN I...

28:49.018 --> 28:53.943
CAN I CALL YOU
IF I HAVE QUESTIONS?

28:53.943 --> 28:56.485
WELL...

28:56.485 --> 28:59.819
I SUPPOSE.

28:59.819 --> 29:01.490
IF YOU MUST.

29:12.421 --> 29:14.083
THANKS FOR HAVING MY BACK
IN THERE.

29:14.083 --> 29:16.005
YOU CAN'T LET HER TALK TO YOU
LIKE THAT.

29:16.005 --> 29:17.176
I KNOW.

29:17.176 --> 29:18.968
WELL,
SO DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT.

29:18.968 --> 29:20.299
I CAN'T.
WELL, YOU HAVE TO.

29:20.299 --> 29:21.971
CALLIE AND I
ARE SPLITTING UP.

29:24.934 --> 29:27.386
AND THERE ARE A LOT OF REASONS
WHY IT HAPPENED,

29:27.386 --> 29:28.938
BUT TAKING THIS FELLOWSHIP

29:28.938 --> 29:31.060
MIGHT'VE BEEN THE NAIL
IN THE COFFIN.

29:31.060 --> 29:34.153
I TRADED MY MARRIAGE
FOR THIS JOB,

29:34.153 --> 29:36.986
AND IT'S PRETTY MUCH
ALL I HAVE RIGHT NOW,

29:36.986 --> 29:37.987
SO IT HAS TO WORK.

29:37.987 --> 29:40.609
I NEED IT TO WORK.

29:40.609 --> 29:43.162
OKAY.

29:43.162 --> 29:45.164
[ SIGHS ]

29:45.164 --> 29:46.665
NO, SCREW THAT.
IT'S NOT OKAY.

29:46.665 --> 29:48.787
I SAW WHAT HAPPENED IN THERE.
SHE'S GOT IT IN FOR YOU.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.539
SHE'S EITHER LOOKING FOR
A REASON TO FIRE YOU,

29:50.539 --> 29:52.411
OR SHE'S GONNA GRIND YOU DOWN
AND MAKE YOU MISERABLE

29:52.411 --> 29:53.412
TRYING TO PLEASE HER.

29:53.412 --> 29:55.584
SHE'LL PROBABLY FIRE YOU
EITHER WAY.

29:55.584 --> 29:58.918
WHAT DO YOU GOT TO LOSE?

29:58.918 --> 30:01.180
MELISSA?
YEAH?

30:01.180 --> 30:02.922
I BROUGHT THESE FOR YOU.
I TOLD YOU I --

30:02.922 --> 30:04.263
WHAT RANK WERE YOU
WHEN YOU GOT OUT?

30:04.263 --> 30:06.425
PFC.
WELL, I WAS A MAJOR,

30:06.425 --> 30:08.807
SO YOU'RE GONNA LISTEN TO ME
IF FOR NO OTHER REASON

30:08.807 --> 30:09.929
THAN I OUTRANK YOU.

30:09.929 --> 30:13.142
BUT MOSTLY BECAUSE WE HAVE
THIS IN COMMON.

30:13.142 --> 30:14.894
I SERVED, JUST LIKE YOU.

30:14.894 --> 30:17.146
I DID TWO TOURS AS A SURGEON

30:17.146 --> 30:20.439
WITH AN ARMY FORWARD
SURGICAL TEAM.

30:20.439 --> 30:23.152
I GAVE WHAT I HAD TO OFFER.

30:23.152 --> 30:24.283
SO DID YOU.

30:24.283 --> 30:26.075
I PATCHED UP GUYS.

30:26.075 --> 30:28.327
I CAN NO MORE, YOU KNOW,
RE-JIGGER A HARD DRIVE --

30:28.327 --> 30:30.209
REFORMAT.
WHAT?

30:30.209 --> 30:31.620
REFORMAT A HARD DRIVE.

30:31.620 --> 30:33.332
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:35.164 --> 30:38.837
YOU GAVE
WHAT YOU HAD TO GIVE.

30:38.837 --> 30:40.169
YOU SERVED.

30:40.169 --> 30:44.173
AND YOU DESERVE
ALL THE HELP AND GRATITUDE

30:44.173 --> 30:46.345
THAT'S OFFERED TO YOU.

30:46.345 --> 30:48.767
BUT IF YOU THINK
THAT BY ACCEPTING THIS HELP

30:48.767 --> 30:50.269
YOU'RE TAKING IT AWAY FROM
THE NEXT GUY, YOU ARE WRONG.

30:50.269 --> 30:52.181
BUT THERE ARE SO MANY GUYS
OUT THERE.

30:52.181 --> 30:53.432
IF YOU WANT TO MAKE SURE
THESE GUYS GET HELP,

30:53.432 --> 30:54.683
I HAVE FRIENDS AT THE V.A.

30:54.683 --> 30:56.145
YOU CAN VOLUNTEER.

30:56.145 --> 30:58.027
THERE'S SO MUCH YOU CAN DO,

30:58.027 --> 31:01.480
BUT TO START, YOU HAVE TO GET UP
ON YOUR OWN FEET.

31:01.480 --> 31:03.282
THAT IS HOW YOU HELP.

31:03.282 --> 31:06.695
THAT IS HOW YOU SERVE.

31:06.695 --> 31:08.657
UNDERSTOOD?

31:10.579 --> 31:12.661
YES, SIR.

31:17.166 --> 31:18.998
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

31:18.998 --> 31:21.090
Maggie: STARTING
THE NECK INCISION.

31:21.090 --> 31:23.002
HOW OLD DID THIS GUY
SAY HE WAS AGAIN?

31:23.002 --> 31:24.593
Miranda: 42.

31:24.593 --> 31:27.096
HE'S GOT THE ESOPHAGUS
OF AN 80-YEAR-OLD.

31:27.096 --> 31:29.098
YOU WENT JOGGING?

31:29.098 --> 31:31.310
YES, I JOGGED --

31:31.310 --> 31:34.273
HALF A MILE,
AND NOW I CAN BARELY WALK,

31:34.273 --> 31:35.474
AND THAT'S
EMBARRASSING ENOUGH

31:35.474 --> 31:37.016
WITHOUT YOU ACTING LIKE
I TOOK A ROCKET TO THE MOON!

31:37.016 --> 31:39.568
YOU SHOULDN'T BE EMBARRASSED.

31:39.568 --> 31:41.440
I HOPE YOU DON'T GIVE UP.

31:41.440 --> 31:46.075
THE THING IS, NO MATTER WHEN
YOU START SOMETHING LIKE THIS,

31:46.075 --> 31:48.157
IT'S GONNA BE HARD.

31:48.157 --> 31:50.159
JUST, YOU HAVE TO START.

31:50.159 --> 31:51.870
AND TAKE BABY STEPS.

31:51.870 --> 31:54.083
IS THAT A SHORT JOKE?

31:55.084 --> 31:57.126
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
B.P.'s DROPPING.

31:57.126 --> 31:58.127
WHAT THE --

31:58.127 --> 31:59.248
THAT'S A THIRD-DEGREE
A.V. BLOCK.

31:59.248 --> 32:01.090
WE NEED TO TRY TO PACE HIM.
DR. BAILEY, CAN YOU --

32:01.090 --> 32:02.251
NO, I HAVE HIS COLON.

32:02.251 --> 32:03.502
OKAY, HOLD IT, HOLD IT!

32:03.502 --> 32:05.094
BRING THE CRASH CART OVER
FOR TEMPORARY PACING.

32:05.094 --> 32:07.006
TOO LATE -- HE'S CODING.
CRAP -- V-FIB!

32:07.006 --> 32:08.347
[ GRUNTS ]

32:08.347 --> 32:11.220
DR. WARREN, GET THE PADDLES
AND CHARGE TO 150.

32:11.220 --> 32:13.102
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

32:13.102 --> 32:14.683
CLEAR!

32:14.683 --> 32:16.725
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

32:19.108 --> 32:20.359
RESTART CPR.

32:20.359 --> 32:22.151
PUSH ONE OF EPI,
PUSH ONE OF ATROPINE!

32:22.151 --> 32:25.064
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

32:25.064 --> 32:26.195
HOLD COMPRESSIONS!

32:26.195 --> 32:28.447
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

32:29.989 --> 32:31.660
NO, IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

32:31.660 --> 32:34.373
OH,
IT CAN'T BE TOO LATE!

32:34.373 --> 32:36.165
GO AGAIN!

32:37.166 --> 32:38.377
CLEAR!

32:39.168 --> 32:42.211
NO. NO.

32:42.211 --> 32:44.213
WE DID
EVERYTHING WE COULD.

32:47.466 --> 32:49.008
GO AGAIN.

32:49.848 --> 32:51.010
CLEAR.

32:51.010 --> 32:52.681
JEREMY DIED
DURING SURGERY.

32:52.681 --> 32:53.802
I'M SO SORRY.

32:53.802 --> 32:56.185
IT WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
HEARTBURN.

32:56.185 --> 32:58.187
IT WAS JUST HEARTBURN.
IT WAS SUPPOSED TO BE HEARTBURN!

32:58.187 --> 32:59.808
HOW COULD THIS HAPPEN?!
Shh!

32:59.808 --> 33:01.020
[ Crying ]
HOW COULD THIS HAPPEN?!

33:01.020 --> 33:03.362
NO! NO, NO, NO!

33:08.657 --> 33:10.529
HEY. YOU DONE SOON?

33:10.529 --> 33:12.111
LET'S GO HOME.

33:12.111 --> 33:15.664
[ SIGHS ]
YOU MEAN, GO TO YOUR HOUSE.

33:15.664 --> 33:17.246
WHAT?

33:17.246 --> 33:19.828
WELL,
IT'S YOUR HOUSE.

33:19.828 --> 33:22.211
I JUST CRASH THERE,
RIGHT?

33:22.211 --> 33:25.044
I MEAN, YOU NEVER ASKED ME
TO MOVE IN.

33:25.044 --> 33:28.006
YOU NEVER COMPLAINED
BUT NEVER...

33:28.006 --> 33:30.509
DID I DO SOMETHING?

33:30.509 --> 33:32.181
'CAUSE I FEEL LIKE
I'M IN TROUBLE.

33:32.181 --> 33:34.343
NO, I'M IN TROUBLE

33:34.343 --> 33:37.056
'CAUSE WHEN THIS CHANGES
I DON'T HAVE ANYPLACE TO BE.

33:37.056 --> 33:39.478
GOD...

33:39.478 --> 33:43.062
I USED TO BE SO CAREFUL.

33:43.062 --> 33:44.943
WAIT, UM...

33:44.943 --> 33:46.985
WHAT'S CHANGING?

33:46.985 --> 33:48.987
I-I-I THOUGHT
WE WERE GOOD.

33:48.987 --> 33:51.450
YES,
BUT IT ALL CHANGES, ALEX.

33:51.450 --> 33:52.861
IT ALWAYS DOES.

33:52.861 --> 33:55.704
YOU CAN'T HOLD ON TO ANYTHING
THAT YOU DON'T WANT TO LOSE.

33:55.704 --> 34:01.039
RIGHT NOW,
I FEEL LIKE I HAVE...

34:01.039 --> 34:03.922
A BED AND A HOUSE.

34:03.922 --> 34:06.585
AND IT IS SO GOOD.

34:06.585 --> 34:11.090
BUT MY BED ISN'T MY BED.
IT'S YOUR BED.

34:11.090 --> 34:14.843
AND I HATE
THAT I DON'T WANT TO LOSE IT.

34:17.266 --> 34:19.268
[ SIGHS ]

34:19.268 --> 34:21.140
HEY.

34:21.140 --> 34:22.181
LOOK AT ME.

34:22.181 --> 34:23.732
YOU GOT ME.

34:23.732 --> 34:25.484
I SWEAR TO GOD.

34:25.484 --> 34:28.687
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE
EXCEPT HOME WITH YOU.

34:28.687 --> 34:30.489
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:35.114 --> 34:36.195
COME ON.

34:36.195 --> 34:37.656
LET'S GO HOME.

34:37.656 --> 34:39.248
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

34:45.464 --> 34:47.586
DID YOU TAKE THE POT ROAST
OUT OF THE OVEN?

34:47.586 --> 34:48.917
UH, I SHUT THE OVEN OFF

34:48.917 --> 34:50.169
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT THAT THING
TO GET COLD.

34:50.169 --> 34:51.420
I'LL TAKE IT OUT.

34:51.420 --> 34:53.422
REALLY?
YOU'RE NOT REALLY A CHEF.

34:53.422 --> 34:55.634
AND YOU ARE?
I'M BETTER THAN YOU.

34:57.596 --> 34:59.017
WHY WOULD YOU SAY
SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

34:59.017 --> 35:00.429
BECAUSE YOU CALLED
THE POT ROAST A "THING."

35:00.429 --> 35:01.600
BUT IT'S NOT TRUE.

35:01.600 --> 35:03.222
YOU'RE NOT BETTER THAN ME.

35:03.222 --> 35:04.643
HAVE YOU EVER
COOKED A MEAL BEFORE?

35:04.643 --> 35:05.984
OKAY, WAIT, TIME-OUT.

35:09.148 --> 35:10.399
WELL?

35:10.399 --> 35:11.780
WELL, WHAT?

35:11.780 --> 35:13.031
YOU CALLED A TIME-OUT.

35:13.031 --> 35:15.194
YOU HAVE TO SAY SOMETHING
WHEN YOU CALL A TIME-OUT.

35:15.194 --> 35:16.995
THAT'S HOW IT OUT WORKS.
IT IS NOT A MUTE BUTTON.

35:16.995 --> 35:18.997
IT IS RIGHT NOW.
THAT'S NOT HOW IT WORKS.

35:18.997 --> 35:20.289
I NEED A TIME-OUT!

35:20.289 --> 35:23.162
I NEED A BREAK -- FROM YOU,
FROM THE FIGHTING,

35:23.162 --> 35:24.913
FROM THE POT ROAST
BECAUSE THE TABLE ISN'T SET.

35:24.913 --> 35:26.124
THE CANDLES AREN'T LIT.

35:26.124 --> 35:28.006
THE GUESTS ARE GONNA ARRIVE
IN 30 MINUTES.

35:28.006 --> 35:31.340
I STILL NEED TO TAKE A SHOWER.
I NEED A TIME-OUT!

35:33.011 --> 35:34.383
DON'T LOOK AT ME LIKE THAT.

35:34.383 --> 35:36.845
I COULD USE A SHOWER, TOO.

35:40.929 --> 35:42.681
HOW'S THE BABY BOOK?

35:42.681 --> 35:44.183
UM...

35:44.183 --> 35:47.266
IT'S THE SCARIEST THING
I'VE EVER READ.

35:47.266 --> 35:49.978
I WAS A JERK TODAY.

35:49.978 --> 35:52.821
YEAH, YOU WERE.

35:52.821 --> 35:55.113
UH, SO, THIS IS THE PART
WHERE YOU SAY,

35:55.113 --> 35:57.906
"NO, YOU WEREN'T THE JERK.
I WAS THE JERK."

35:57.906 --> 36:00.158
YEAH, BUT I WASN'T,
AND YOU WERE.

36:00.158 --> 36:01.660
[ LAUGHS ]

36:01.660 --> 36:03.582
GET UP.
I WANT TO SIT DOWN.

36:03.582 --> 36:05.083
OKAY.

36:05.083 --> 36:06.995
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:06.995 --> 36:08.417
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

36:08.417 --> 36:09.918
HMM?

36:09.918 --> 36:10.999
[ SIGHS ]

36:10.999 --> 36:12.291
RIGHT?

36:12.291 --> 36:15.003
YOU BUILT THIS?

36:15.003 --> 36:16.345
TWICE, ACTUALLY.

36:16.345 --> 36:18.467
I'M PRETTY SURE
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG

36:18.467 --> 36:19.598
WITH THE DIRECTIONS.

36:21.260 --> 36:23.262
IT'S PERFECT.

36:23.262 --> 36:26.104
YOU DID A GOOD JOB.

36:28.307 --> 36:32.731
YOU'RE GONNA BE
A GREAT DADDY.

36:34.523 --> 36:36.365
THANK YOU.

36:36.365 --> 36:38.697
THANK YOU.

36:40.319 --> 36:43.992
I'M DYING.
I'M JUST GONNA DROP DEAD.

36:43.992 --> 36:45.494
OH,
WE'VE TALKED ABOUT YOU

36:45.494 --> 36:47.746
READING HORROR STORIES
BEFORE BED.

36:47.746 --> 36:49.328
I DON'T WANT TO GET PUNCHED
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

36:49.328 --> 36:50.499
BECAUSE YOU'RE HAVING
NIGHTMARES.

36:50.499 --> 36:52.090
I RAN MY LABS YESTERDAY

36:52.090 --> 36:54.172
AFTER WE FOUND
MR. WEAVER'S TUMOR.

36:54.172 --> 36:57.005
LOOK,
LDL CHOLESTEROL -- 178.

36:57.005 --> 36:59.428
HDL -- 26.

36:59.428 --> 37:02.050
TRIGLYCERIDES -- 320.

37:02.050 --> 37:03.432
GLUCOSE -- 152.

37:03.432 --> 37:05.223
WELL,
THIS EXPLAINS THE JOGGING.

37:05.223 --> 37:06.555
I'M SUCH A HYPOCRITE.

37:06.555 --> 37:09.438
I TELL PEOPLE EVERY DAY
HOW IMPORTANT IT IS

37:09.438 --> 37:11.610
TO EAT RIGHT
AND TO EXERCISE.

37:11.610 --> 37:15.233
I JUST THINK I'M SAYING IT
SO MUCH, I-I'M NOT HEARING IT.

37:15.233 --> 37:16.234
YOU'RE NOT DYING.

37:16.234 --> 37:17.986
THE NUMBERS AREN'T GREAT,
BUT --

37:17.986 --> 37:20.068
NO,
I HAVE TO MAKE SOME CHANGES.

37:20.068 --> 37:22.200
[ SIGHS ]
STARTING NOW.

37:22.200 --> 37:24.162
BUT -- BUT NOT RIGHT NOW.

37:24.162 --> 37:25.414
YOU GO FOR A JOG
RIGHT THIS SECOND,

37:25.414 --> 37:27.165
I DON'T THINK YOU'D EVER BE ABLE
TO WALK AGAIN.

37:27.165 --> 37:28.417
OW!

37:28.417 --> 37:29.828
OKAY, I [CHUCKLES]

37:29.828 --> 37:31.580
I DID MENTION NOT WANTING TO BE
PUNCHED, DIDN'T I?

37:31.580 --> 37:34.423
YEAH, UH,
BUT IT'S GOOD CARDIO.

37:34.423 --> 37:35.584
[ STAMMERS ]

37:35.584 --> 37:37.045
OH, LIKE THAT REALLY HURT.
THAT HURT?

37:39.338 --> 37:41.590
[ WATER RUNNING ]

37:47.936 --> 37:50.559
Meredith: THE ABCs OF TRAUMA
ARE A HANDY TOOL

37:50.559 --> 37:52.771
FOR KEEPING A PATIENT ALIVE.

37:55.314 --> 37:57.155
BUT THEY'RE ONLY
A STARTING POINT.

37:57.155 --> 37:58.567
HI?

37:58.567 --> 38:00.989
OH.

38:00.989 --> 38:02.781
UH, HELLO.

38:03.952 --> 38:07.035
UM,
I JUST RANG THE BELL.

38:07.035 --> 38:08.747
NO ONE ANSWERED.

38:08.747 --> 38:11.209
UM, THEY DID SAY 8:00,
RIGHT?

38:11.209 --> 38:12.751
THEY DID, YEAH.

38:12.751 --> 38:14.252
THE TABLE IS SET.

38:14.252 --> 38:15.504
YEAH, IT IS.

38:15.504 --> 38:17.085
IT'S...STRANGE.

38:17.085 --> 38:20.549
ONCE THE PATIENT'S AIRWAY,
BREATHING, AND CIRCULATION

38:20.549 --> 38:22.681
ARE ALL CLEAR
AND ACCOUNTED FOR,

38:22.681 --> 38:24.763
THE REAL WORK BEGINS --
THE MESSY WORK.

38:24.763 --> 38:25.924
I BROUGHT WINE.

38:25.924 --> 38:27.976
I'M AN ALCOHOLIC.

38:27.976 --> 38:29.097
[ WINGS FLAPPING ]

38:29.097 --> 38:30.429
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

38:30.429 --> 38:33.812
THIS WAS A MISTAKE.
I'M GONNA GO.

38:34.643 --> 38:36.525
LOOK, I SCREWED UP!

38:39.398 --> 38:41.239
I-I-I SCREWED UP.

38:41.239 --> 38:42.991
I-I'M SORRY.

38:44.743 --> 38:48.286
LOOK, 31 YEARS AGO,
I HAD A KID.

38:48.286 --> 38:50.449
AND NOBODY TOLD ME.

38:50.449 --> 38:54.953
I'VE KNOWN YOU FOR ONLY,
WHAT, TWO MONTHS.

38:54.953 --> 38:56.755
TWO MONTHS.

38:56.755 --> 39:00.509
MOST PARENTS MESS UP A LOT
IN THOSE FIRST FEW MONTHS,

39:00.509 --> 39:03.842
AND IT'S FINE BECAUSE
T-THEIR KID'S TOO YOUNG

39:03.842 --> 39:06.134
TO -- TO NOTICE
OR REMEMBER.

39:06.134 --> 39:09.968
BUT YOU -- I HURT YOU,
AND I-I-I KNOW THAT.

39:09.968 --> 39:12.350
AND ALL I WANT TO DO...

39:12.350 --> 39:15.564
IS JUST TAKE IT BACK,
OKAY?

39:15.564 --> 39:20.068
YOU'VE GOT THE WRONG IDEA.

39:20.068 --> 39:23.982
I'M NOT ANGRY WITH YOU
FOR BEING A BAD FATHER.

39:23.982 --> 39:26.364
YOU'RE NOT MY DAD.

39:26.364 --> 39:30.078
YOU ARE JUST A MAN
WHO SLEPT WITH A WOMAN

39:30.078 --> 39:32.370
AND MADE IT POSSIBLE
FOR ME TO BE BORN.

39:32.370 --> 39:35.584
[ SCOFFS ]
MY DAD IS MY PRESENT.

39:35.584 --> 39:39.047
YOU ARE MY PAST.
YOU ARE MY GENETIC HISTORY.

39:39.047 --> 39:42.050
I DIDN'T NEED YOU
TO BE A GOOD FATHER.

39:42.050 --> 39:45.213
I JUST NEEDED YOU
TO BE HONEST WITH ME...

39:45.213 --> 39:47.005
FROM THE START,

39:47.005 --> 39:48.637
INSTEAD OF LETTING ME
WALK AROUND HERE FOR WEEKS

39:48.637 --> 39:53.101
LIKE A FOOL, WITHOUT A CLUE,
LETTING ME CONFIDE IN YOU.

39:53.101 --> 39:56.014
♪ ...LOOK AT YOURSELF,
LOOK AT YOURSELF ♪

39:56.014 --> 39:57.976
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

39:57.976 --> 40:00.569
♪ BABY, LOOK AT US NOW,
LOOK AT US NOW ♪

40:00.569 --> 40:02.981
AND I'LL NEVER BE ANYTHING
BUT SORRY FOR THAT.

40:02.981 --> 40:05.153
THERE'S NO TELLING
HOW LONG IT'S GOING TO TAKE

40:05.153 --> 40:06.404
TO CLEAN UP THAT CHAOS...

40:06.404 --> 40:08.076
OKAY.

40:08.076 --> 40:10.408
GOOD NIGHT.

40:10.408 --> 40:13.201
...ONCE YOU'VE BEGUN...

40:13.201 --> 40:15.123
[ LAUGHS ] SORRY.

40:15.123 --> 40:18.086
I THINK I MUST'VE LOST TRACK
OF TIME.

40:18.086 --> 40:21.209
I HOPE YOU BROUGHT
A, UH, AN APPETITE.

40:21.209 --> 40:25.133
...BECAUSE SOMETIMES YOU DON'T
KNOW WHAT YOU'RE IN FOR.

40:25.133 --> 40:26.885
[ SIGHS ]
CAN I TALK TO YOU?

40:26.885 --> 40:28.717
ACTUALLY,
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU.

40:28.717 --> 40:31.139
DR. HERMAN, I WASN'T KIDDING
WHEN I SAID THAT I --

40:31.139 --> 40:33.311
THAT I -- THAT I WANTED
THIS FELLOWSHIP,

40:33.311 --> 40:36.104
AND TODAY'S SURGERY ONLY
CONFIRMED THAT MORE FOR ME.

40:36.104 --> 40:37.395
CLOSE THE DOOR.

40:37.395 --> 40:40.268
[ SIGHS ]

40:40.268 --> 40:45.484
BUT NO MATTER HOW MUCH I NEED
OR WANT THIS FELLOWSHIP,

40:45.484 --> 40:48.406
I REFUSE TO SPEND THE YEAR
WITH YOU SPEAKING TO ME

40:48.406 --> 40:50.328
THE WAY
THAT YOU SPEAK TO ME.

40:50.328 --> 40:52.240
WE WON'T HAVE A YEAR
TOGETHER.

40:55.073 --> 40:56.835
FINE.

40:56.835 --> 40:57.956
GREAT. THANKS.

40:57.956 --> 41:00.288
I'LL BE DEAD
IN SIX MONTHS.

41:00.288 --> 41:03.582
YOU DON'T KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO FACE.

41:03.582 --> 41:05.924
I HAVE A BRAIN TUMOR.

41:05.924 --> 41:09.257
IT'S INOPERABLE.

41:09.257 --> 41:11.349
I THOUGHT I HAD LONGER,

41:11.349 --> 41:13.512
BUT IT'S GROWING.

41:13.512 --> 41:18.937
SOON, I WILL SHOW SYMPTOMS,
AND AFTER THAT, I WILL DIE.

41:21.399 --> 41:23.481
WHO KNOWS ABOUT THIS?

41:23.481 --> 41:26.064
HUNT?
UH, ANYONE?

41:26.064 --> 41:28.106
FETAL SURGERY
IS A NEW FIELD.

41:28.106 --> 41:30.318
THE FEW OF US
WHO ARE PRACTICING IT

41:30.318 --> 41:33.031
ARE BASICALLY INVENTING IT
AS WE GO ALONG.

41:33.031 --> 41:34.663
THE THINGS I KNOW,

41:34.663 --> 41:37.075
THE THINGS I SCRIBBLE DOWN
IN THE MARGINS, NO ONE HAS THEM.

41:37.075 --> 41:40.919
THEY'RE NOT IN ANY TEXTBOOK.
THEY'RE ONLY IN MY BRAIN.

41:40.919 --> 41:45.003
SO I CAN FIGHT TO WRITE PAPERS
AND TRY TO GET THEM PUBLISHED,

41:45.003 --> 41:47.295
OR I CAN USE
THE TIME I HAVE LEFT

41:47.295 --> 41:51.389
TO TRY TO TEACH YOU A YEAR'S
WORTH OF MEDICINE IN SIX MONTHS.

41:53.011 --> 41:54.302
OR...

41:54.302 --> 41:56.514
YOU CAN TELL HUNT
AND THE BOARD,

41:56.514 --> 41:59.057
AND IT ALL GOES AWAY
FOREVER.

41:59.057 --> 42:01.139
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT SECRETS

42:01.139 --> 42:02.731
THE BODY IN FRONT OF YOU
HOLDS...

42:02.731 --> 42:05.483
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO FEEL ABOUT THIS.

42:06.985 --> 42:08.907
WELL,
HURRY UP AND DECIDE.

42:08.907 --> 42:10.949
WE DON'T HAVE
ANY TIME TO WASTE.

42:10.949 --> 42:14.913
...AND WHETHER,
BY THE TIME IT'S ALL OVER,

42:14.913 --> 42:17.495
IF THERE'S ANYTHING LEFT
WORTH SAVING.
